article.headline: Florida 79, Presbyterian 38
article.story: GAINESVILLE, Fla. -- Chandler Parsons scored 21 points and Alex Tyus and Erik Murphy each had double-doubles as Florida dominated Presbyterian 79-38 on Wednesday night. The Gators (10-3) scored 13 of the game's first 14 points and led the Blue Hose (2-12) by more than 30 for most of the second half. Parsons' all-around game as Florida's sixth man included two 3-pointers and three dunks. Tyus' 16 points and 13 rebounds marked his first double-double since the season opener. Murphy, who had been battling a shoulder injury, set career highs with 16 points and 11 boards off the bench. The Gators outrebounded the Blue Hose 51-29 and had a 46-12 edge in points in the paint. Florida guard Ray Shipman (knee) missed his second straight game, and center Kenny Kadji (back) sat out for the fifth time in six games. Jake Troyli led Presbyterian with 14 points.
